HEADWORD: Salvor
<hw>Sal"vor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Salvation</er>, <er>Save</er>]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who
assists in saving a ship or goods at sea, without being under special
obligation to do so.</def> <rj><au>Wheaton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
